{
  "id": "1780958824199",
  "title": "Account setup revamp",
  "summary": "Does a shorter setup flow increase wizard completion? No, it didn't.",
  "slug": "account-setup-revamp",
  "product_area": "Onboarding",
  "test_topic": "Activation",
  "hypothesis": "This experiment creates a new account setup experiment for 50% of new signups. This account setup flow is designed to be shorter, more aesthetically pleasing, and delightful to use. We are also adding a new step prompting the user to confirm their branding, which is optional. We believe this will lead to earlier personalization and better overall activation.",
  "results": "Treatment failed to meaningfully outperform control. Decision: ship control group. New branding experience showed a 10%+ conversion increase vs. legacy branding flow.",
  "learning": "Mobile responsiveness was a critical issue — shrunken components and partially hidden navigation made it hard to progress on mobile. The new branding experience showed promise and has been shipped to all users independently.",
  "notes": "<p>Industry data no longer collected as a step in setup — gathered via BuiltWith in background and classified by DS model (CompanyWebsiteAnalysis table). </p><p>Mobile responsiveness is critical. </p><ul class=\"list-disc pl-4\"><li><p>Shrunken components on mobile made data input and progressing to next steps incredibly hard.</p></li><li><p>Partially hidden navigation left mobile users unable to progress through setup for a period of the experiment.</p></li><li><p>Responsiveness can no longer be an afterthought, and needs to be part of solution design. </p></li></ul><p>Delight without utility creates friction.</p><ul class=\"list-disc pl-4\"><li><p>The colorful side panel was intended to create a more engaging experience, but the data suggests it distracted/confused/overwhelmed users rather than help/motivate them to move forward.</p></li><li><p> 'Delightful' additions need to earn their place by being directly helpful. </p></li></ul><p>AI fallbacks are non-negotiable. </p><ul class=\"list-disc pl-4\"><li><p>Parts of the experience relied on AI-generated content without graceful fallbacks for long wait periods or failure states. </p></li><li><p>When AI was unavailable or underperforming, users hit semi-dead ends. Any AI-dependent feature needs a reliable fallback before it ships.</p></li></ul><p></p>",
